node.text: With Singapore slowly easing its circuit breaker measures, here’s a quick list of what opens on May 5 and May 12 – and what you can finally do and what you still can’t. For those itching to get a haircut, we’re almost there! But sorry, bubble tea fans, you’ll have to wait a little longer. Bookmark and share with your friends and family. And visit CNA for more details! #circuitbreaker #bubbletea #haircut (Art: Kenneth Choy)

Daiso will still closed. Although they sell essential products but because their price is too competitive. Also those sell toiletries at people's park market. They also affect bigger player bottom line. Only Big Brother's shop can open. Can sell cigarettes but not cakes.

Madam Lee May Hua had a point in Zthe recent parliamentary meeting about the restriction with the opening of traditional chinese medical shops. It is a accepted way of life for the older Singaporean citizens to patronise these establishments for any minor ailments. Without the service of these facilities in their immediate neighbourhood really hinder the usual lifestyles of these elderly citizens. The Government seems to more consider the likes and feeling of younger people and ignoring the welfare of the senior citizens. May the younger ministers be aw
